definition.value: One of the twenty-four Governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is an inland province, situated in the centre of the country.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in west-central Tunisia on the frontier with Algeria.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in south-western Tunisia, bordering Algeria.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in north-western Tunisia, bordering Algeria.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in central-eastern Tunisia.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in northern Tunisia.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in south-eastern Tunisia.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in north-eastern Tunisia.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in north-eastern Tunisia.
One of the governorates of Tunisia.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in central Tunisia.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in northern Tunisia.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in north-eastern Tunisia.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in southern Tunisia, bordering Algeria and Libya.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in western Tunisia, bordering Algeria.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in northern Tunisia.
One of the twenty-four governorates (provinces) of Tunisia. It is situated in north-eastern Tunisia.
One of the districts of Libya. Its capital is Ghat.
A district (Arabic: Sha'biya) of Libya.
One of the districts of Libya. It is in the north-east of the country. Its capital is Al Bayda.
One of the districts of Libya. It is in the south of the country. Its capital is Murzuk.
One of the districts of Libya, in the northwest, south of Tripoli.
One of the districts of Libya. It is in the centre of the country. Its capital is Houn.
A sha'biyah (district) in northwestern Libya. The capital is the city of Misratah. In 2007 the district was enlarged to include what had been the Bani Walid District.
One of the districts of Libya. Its capital is Al Jawf.
One of the districts of Libya. Its capital is Nalut.

A district of northeastern Libya, lying on the Mediterranean Sea coast. Its administrative seat is the city of El Marj. In the 2007 administrative reorganization the territory formerly in Al Hizam Al Akhdar District was transferred to Al Marj.
One of the districts of Libya. In 2007 the district was enlarged to include the twentysix Basic People's Congresses,(townships), of what had been the Tarhuna Wa Msalata District.
One of the districts of Libya. It is in the northwest of the country. Its capital is Zuwarah.
A district of Libya.
One of the districts of Libya. It is located in the center of the country. The capital is Sabha.
One of the districts of Libya. In 2007 the district was enlarged to include what had been the Ajdabiya District.
One of the districts of Libya, which lies in the north of the country and borders the Gulf of Sidra. Its capital is the city of Surt.

One of the districts in Libya. It is located in the north-western part of the country. Its capital is Az Zawiyah. Since the 2007 reorganization of Libyan districts, the former district of Sabratha Wa Surman has been part of Az Zawiyah District.
A district of Libya.
One of the districts of Libya.
One of the districts of Libya in the central-west part of the country. Its capital is Brak. The area is mostly desert.
One of the districts of Libya. It is in the northeast of the country. Its capital is Darnah. In 2007 the district was enlarged to include what had been the Al Qubah District.
An inland region of Eritrea, in the west of the country. Its capital is Keren.

One of the six regions of Eritrea. It is the smallest region in area, and contains the major city and national capital, Asmara. The region is inland, and borders Anseba to the north-west, Northern Red Sea region to the north-east, Southern region to the south, and Gash-Barka to the west.

One of the six regions of Eritrea. It is situated in the south-west of the country, bordering the Anseba region to the north, and the Central and Southern regions to the east; the county of Sudan lies to the west and Ethiopia to the south.

A region of Eritrea. It lies along a portion of the national border with Ethiopia. It shares its western border with the region of Gash-Barka, its north with Maakel (central) and its eastern with the Northern Red Sea region.
One of the six main regions of Eritrea. It lies along the southern half of the Red Sea, and contains the coastal city of Asseb. It borders the Northern Red Sea region.

One of the nine ethnic divisions (kililoch) of Ethiopia, and is the homeland of the Afar people. Formerly known as Region 2, its current capital is Asayita; a new capital named Semera on the paved Awash - Asseb highway is under construction.
One of the nine ethnic divisions (kililoch) of Ethiopia.

One of the nine ethnic divisions (kililoch) of Ethiopia. Region was created from the westernmost portion of the Gojjam province (the part north of the Abay River), and the northwestern portion of the Welega Province (the part south of the Abay).
One of the nine ethnic divisions (kililoch) of Ethiopia. Its capital is Gambela. Lying between the Baro and Akobo Rivers, the western part of Gambela includes the Baro salient.

One of the nine ethnic divisions (kililoch) of Ethiopia. An enclave in Oromia Region. It includes the former Arsi Province along with portions of the former Bale, Hararghe, Illubabor, Kaffa, Shewa, Sidamo, and Welega provinces. Its current capital is Adama.
One of the nine ethnic divisions (kililoch) of Ethiopia.

The eastern-most of the nine ethnic divisions (kililoch) of Ethiopia. The region borders Kenya to the south-west, the Ethopian regions of Oromia, Afar and Dire Dawa (Diridhawa) to the west, Djibouti to the north and Somalia to the north, east and south.
